{"cells": [{"cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": ["# Learning APIs with Python 🐍\n", "\n", "In this notebook, we will learn how to work with **APIs (Application Programming Interfaces)** using Python.\n", "We will use free APIs that **do not require any API key**, sample APIs with public test keys, and also demonstrate live APIs where you can use your own key."]}, {"cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": ["## Setup\n", "We will use the `requests` library to send HTTP requests and fetch data from APIs."]}, {"cell_type": "code", "metadata": {}, "source": ["!pip install requests"]}, {"cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": ["## Example: Live OpenWeatherMap API (Requires Your Key)\n", "\n", "You can get a free API key by signing up at [OpenWeatherMap](https://openweathermap.org/api). Once you have your key, you can fetch real-time weather for any city."]}, {"cell_type": "code", "metadata": {}, "source": ["# Replace with your OpenWeatherMap API key\n", "api_key = 'YOUR_API_KEY_HERE'  # <-- Put your key here\n", "city = 'Berlin'\n", "weather_url = f'[https://api.openweathermap.org/data/2.5/weather?q={city}&appid={api_key}&units=metric'\n](https://api.openweathermap.org/data/2.5/weather?q={city}&appid={api_key}&units=metric'\n)", "\n", "response = requests.get(weather_url)\n", "data = response.json()\n", "\n", "if response.status_code == 200:\n", "    print(f"City: {data['name']}")\n", "    print(f"Weather: {data['weather'][0]['description']}")\n", "    print(f"Temperature: {data['main']['temp']}°C")\n", "    print(f"Humidity: {data['main']['humidity']}%")\n", "else:\n", "    print(f"Error: {response.status_code}, {data.get('message') or ''}")"]}, {"cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": ["### Explanation:\n", "- Replace `'YOUR_API_KEY_HERE'` with your actual OpenWeatherMap API key.\n", "- This fetches live weather data in metric units for any city you choose.\n", "- `data['weather'][0]['description']` gives the weather condition, `data['main']['temp']` the temperature."]}, {"cell_type": "markdown", "metadata": {}, "source": ["## Summary of API Types Covered\n", "- Free APIs with no key: JSONPlaceholder, Random User, Dog CEO, MetaWeather, CoinGecko\n", "- Sample API with public test key: OpenWeatherMap sample key\n", "- Live API requiring your own key: OpenWeatherMap live weather data\n", "\n", "You can now fetch and explore real-time data interactively in Jupyter."]}]}
